1. Erythromycin thiocyanate: Prices have remained broadly stable with a single-digit increase YTD, supported by balanced supply and demand. Management expects prices to remain steady in 2H25; 
2. 7-ACA & 7-ADCA: Prices have also remained relatively stable since the beginning of the year, with similar stability expected in the coming months; 
3. 6-APA: Prices have declined YTD, due to softer demand (notably lower amoxicillin usage) and management's strategy of using lower prices to strengthen competitive positioning and deter smaller entrants into the market. However, management expects improvement in 4Q25, with peak-season demand likely to support a rebound.
